## Review Criteria

Each review will evaluate the governance framework against the following criteria:

### Efficiency

- Time spent on documentation vs. implementation
- Decision-making speed
- Task completion velocity
- Tool call efficiency

### Compliance

- Adherence to established processes
- Documentation completeness
- Error handling consistency
- Data access logging coverage

### Developer Experience

- Framework learning curve
- Documentation clarity
- Process friction points
- Developer satisfaction

### Adaptability

- Ease of modifying framework components
- Response to new requirements
- Integration with new tools and workflows

## Review Process

### Preparation

1. Collect metrics from the past period:
   - Task completion rates
   - Documentation coverage
   - Error resolution times
   - Developer feedback

2. Prepare review materials:
   - Metrics summary
   - Key challenges identified
   - Improvement suggestions

### Review Meeting

1. Review metrics and identify trends (30 minutes)
2. Discuss key challenges and successes (45 minutes)
3. Evaluate each framework component (60 minutes)
4. Develop improvement proposals (45 minutes)

### Post-Review

1. Document findings in decision-logs.mdc
2. Implement approved changes to framework
3. Update framework documentation
4. Communicate changes to all stakeholders

